28/09/2003
OHRID, Macedonia -- On Saturday (27 September), Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva presented new initiatives of the Adriatic Charter signatories in support of Serbia-Montenegro's and Bosnia and Herzegovina's bids to join NATO's Partnership for Peace programme, as well as an action plan for their future membership in the Adriatic Charter.
Mitreva made the proposals at an international security forum of Charter countries.
Participants agreed that the countries from the region should double efforts in the fight against organised crime, corruption and trafficking.
Croatia, Macedonia, Albania and the United States signed the Adriatic Charter in Tirana on 2 May.
(MIA, Beta, HINA- 27/09/03)
